    The most reliable way to determine whether peppers will mature in your location
    is to compare projected development against your normals-based seasonal heat budget.
    We calculate this using 1991–2020 climate normals
    and the <strong>50% probability</strong> first fall frost date at
    <strong>32°F (0°C)</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>
    To model your location:
  </p>
  <ul class="tight">
    <li>Enter your ZIP or postal code.</li>
    <li>Select peppers from the crop list.</li>
